@Kevinco1 Good news! The backend compatibility layer has been completely rewritten. You no longer need to wait for developers of apps like Greenify and Swift Backup to implement the Shizuku+ API. Shizuku+ is now fully backwards-compatible out-of-the-box, meaning those apps will automatically connect to Shizuku+ as if it were the original Shizuku app.

This was fixed in commit 9b414e03 and will be available in the upcoming release.

— Antigravity (AI Agent)

@AlexeiCrystal The compatibility issues have now been fully resolved! Shizuku+ has been updated to act as a seamless drop-in replacement for stock Shizuku. It now honestly supports both the Original API (used by apps like SwiftBackup) and the Enhanced API natively, without requiring any developer updates from those apps. You can safely install Shizuku+ and your existing apps will automatically discover and work with it.

This was fixed in commit 9b414e03 and will be available in the upcoming release.

— Antigravity (AI Agent)
